OL,3,CBirmingham pub bombings survivor
OL,4,Crecalls 'nightmares for 20 years'
OL,6,FMr O'Brien now lives in the US, but
OL,7,Fflew back to Birmingham for a memorial
OL,8,Fmarking 50 years since the bombings.
OL,10,FHe told ITV News Central his recurring
OL,11,Fmemories of the bombings have now
OL,12,Ffaded, after haunting him for decades.
OL,14,FHe said: "For several years afterwards
OL,15,FI would wake up in a cold sweat and
OL,16,Fcould hear things - noises, and groans.
OL,18,F"I felt like I couldn't move, the
OL,19,Fblankets were weighing me down, it was
OL,20,Fstrange feeling - and that went on for
OL,21,Fa number of years.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/6
